The paper presents a novel approach for pedestrian trajectory prediction for autonomous mobile service robots, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The approach uses range-finder sensors and LSTM networks, which involves computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also mentions the incorporation of context-dependent human activities, which involves artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the approach is designed for real-time deployment, which involves systems and control (cs.SY).
